This chowder was absolutley incredible!!! I made it for a group of people and they could not get over it. I did make a few alterations. I used fresh roasted corn. It took 20 ears to get 8 cups. I husked and brushed them with olive oil and roasted them for 40 minutes at 400 degrees. They came out just right. Cutting all the corn from the cob is labor intensive, but if you have some help it gets done in no time. The result is well worth it! The other alteration that I made was using fresh lobster meat. I boiled three 1 -1 1/4 pound lobsters and used all the meat (claws and tails). This was easy and delicious. Living on Cape Cod I could not use frozen lobster or frozen corn. I also added a small jalapeno pepper from the garden and added a little more cayenne pepper, the tastes melded perfectly. I will definitly make this recipe again. It was amazing. My family said it was the best corn chowder they have ever had!

